# Copy to `server/.env` for secrets. This file is also loaded by `smtpMailer.ts` as defaults

# (then `server/.env` and repo-root `.env` override). Do not put real passwords in the

# committed copy—use placeholders here and real values in `server/.env` (gitignored).



# --- Auth (required in production) ---

# At least 32 characters. Example: openssl rand -base64 48

JWT_SECRET="This is a secret key for the JWT token. No one can ever know this top secret. Don't you forget it!"

# Optional; default 7d

# JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d



# --- HTTP / deployment ---

# Comma-separated browser origins allowed to call this API (must match your SPA URL exactly).

# Production: required. Development: optional (defaults to http(s)://localhost and 127.0.0.1).

# CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:5173

# Behind a reverse proxy so rate limits and logs see real client IPs:

# TRUST_PROXY=1



# Mailtrap Email Testing: https://mailtrap.io → Email Testing → SMTP (sandbox inbox only).
MAILTRAP_USER=b7e7f3b51dc3d8
MAILTRAP_PASS=b9012cc833ea34
MAIL_FROM=noreply@localhost

# Optional
# MAIL_REPLY_TO=

# If SMTP_HOST and SMTP_PORT are both set, they take precedence over MAILTRAP_*.
